    "Variation in tool type (such as whether tools combined existing biological foundation models with other machine learning prediction algorithms or whether they were trained to process sequence, structure or clinical data).",
    "C. Tool misuse potential (meaning that, when uncertain, we preferentially included tools which could plausibly possess misuse-relevant capabilities as described in our rubrics).",
    "This was done by assigning individual researchers to a category, who then narrowed it down according to the principles above.",
    "As diverse tools were being compared with multiple criteria, some decisions were challenging and tool selection was often discussed and iterated several times within the wider team in order to come to a conclusion.",
    "A total of 57 final tools were determined to be in this 'minimal set' of state-of-the-art tools given their assessed capabilities."
